last_episode_to_air.name: Wreck the Malls
last_episode_to_air.overview: The mall is taken over by a terrorist Mall Santa, trapping Trent's children inside, and locking the rest of the team out of doing some last-minute Christmas shopping.

name: NTSF:SD:SUV::
overview: NTSF:SD:SUV:: – meaning National Terrorism Strike Force: San Diego: Sport Utility Vehicle:: – is a quarter-hour format American television comedy that parodies the police procedural and action film genres.

episodes.name: One Cabeza, Two Cabeza, Three Cabeza...DEAD!
episodes.overview: A new alcoholic energy drink is killing University of San Diego Students. NTSF must team up with the Food and Drug Administration, despite their mutual mistrust, to follow a lead.

episodes.name: The Birthday Party That Was Neither
episodes.overview: Each member of NTSF gets a mysterious call from a person who claims they have secret information about them. Unbeknownst to the other members, they each must bring a million dollars to a warehouse, leaving Kove alone at NTSF HQ. When the caller is finally revealed, the team gets a blast from the past.

episodes.name: Exes and Oh-No's!
episodes.overview: Trent's ex surfaces after a sex change and plots to steal a San Diego treasure. Elsewhere, Piper's pick for book club goes unread.

episodes.name: The Risky Business of Being Alone in Your Home
episodes.overview: Trent is suspended and forced to spend time at home, where terrorists plot to attack him. His replacement, an old nemesis, is a hit at the NTSF.

episodes.name: Dolphinnegan's Wake
episodes.overview: Trent tracks a dolphin serial killer and turns to a similar murderer in captivity for advice on catching his target.

episodes.name: Tijuana, We've Got a Problem
episodes.overview: Space-shuttle plans are stolen and sold to Mexico, so the team must retrieve them before the U.S. loses the space race.

episodes.name: Full Hauser
episodes.overview: Trent plans a cruise for the NTSF team, but he's got ulterior motives to capture a terrorist rumored to be hiding out on the ship. Meanwhile, Piper brings her new fiancé along for the trip.

episodes.name: Up Periscope, Down With San Diego
episodes.overview: The team must prevent an attack on San Diego by Japanese soldiers who've been lost at sea for decades.

episodes.name: Cause for ConCERN
episodes.overview: Trent visits a peaceful parallel dimension where terrorism doesn't exist and decides to help his doppelgänger restore balance to the world.

episodes.name: Piper Doesn't Live Here Anymore
episodes.overview: Piper is brainwashed to become an assassin, and her mission is to hunt down her NTSF teammates. Elsewhere, Jessie catches the eye of a model photographer.

episodes.name: Twistin' the Night Away
episodes.overview: Trent tracks the source of strange occurrences, including a hostage situation with SUVs and Sam's partnership with a creepy new team member.

episodes.name: I Left My Heart in Someone's Cooler
episodes.overview: Terrorists plan to bomb the San Diego Day parade in a plot that involves the President of the Navy. Elsewhere, Alphonse is tasked with finding the perfect gift for Trent's kids.

episodes.name: 16 Hop Street
episodes.overview: Trent and Piper go undercover in school to find a kidnapper.

episodes.name: The Real Bicycle Thief
episodes.overview: Trent hunts for restaurant terrorists and goes undercover in the Swedish pedicab-racing circuit.

episodes.name: Sabbath-tage
episodes.overview: Sam takes on a terrorist who attacks the city on a Saturday.

episodes.name: Lights, Camera, Assassination
episodes.overview: A teen idol shadows Trent and Alphonse during the hunt for a killer who targets Hollywood directors; Kove develops a podcast.

episodes.name: Time Angels
episodes.overview: Anti-terrorism time travelers join the team to prevent crimes.

episodes.name: Whack-A-Mole
episodes.overview: The team is blamed for the death of Gary the Killer Whale.

episodes.name: Robot Town
episodes.overview: Trent visits Robot Town to clear S.A.M. of murder charges.

episodes.name: Comic-Con-Flict
episodes.overview: Comic fans pose a threat to authors at a San Diego convention.

episodes.name: The Return of Dragon Shumway
episodes.overview: Piper's fiancee has a difficult time letting go of his ninja past.

episodes.name: Family Dies
episodes.overview: Trent has to kill his father.

episodes.name: Prairie Dog Companion
episodes.overview: Jessie and Sam head underground to infiltrate a group of crazed book sellers who are intent on destroying the Internet.

episodes.name: Wasilla Hills Cop
episodes.overview: Alphonse goes home to Alaska to investigate his partner's death and repair a rift with his father.

episodes.name: The NTSF:SD:SUV::HISS Infomercial
episodes.overview: The NTSF gang show off their home security system and iPhone app.

episodes.name: Christmas Activity
episodes.overview: While celebrating Christmas together at Kove's house, the team is attacked by the evil Alaskan Santa Claus.

episodes.name: Inertia
episodes.overview: A bomb on a bus is set to explode if the bus goes over zero miles an hour. A condensed edit of the 2012 web series. Guest stars: Matt Braunger, Echo Kellum

episodes.name: Comic Con-Air
episodes.overview: Comic-Con's worst villains get loose on a plane.

episodes.name: Hawaii Die-0
episodes.overview: A commencement address poses a great danger to the President of the Navy.

episodes.name: Extra Terrorist-rial
episodes.overview: Trent's nephew befriends a seemingly benign alien, but the NTSF team think it's dangerous.

episodes.name: Burn After Killing
episodes.overview: Commander Kove's little black book is stolen.

episodes.name: TGI Murder
episodes.overview: The team tries to protect a restaurant chain from violent competitors.

episodes.name: The Great Train Stoppery
episodes.overview: Time Angels travel to the Wild West.

episodes.name: A Hard Drive to Swallow
episodes.overview: S.A.M. is taken prisoner by an anti-robot group and NTSF must find a way to rescue him.

episodes.name: Unfrozen Agent Man
episodes.overview: An NTSF agent from the past is called upon to capture an escaped criminal.

episodes.name: Trading Faces
episodes.overview: Sam and Trent exchange faces to thwart a terrorist organization.

episodes.name: U-KO'ed
episodes.overview: When Alphonse is captured in an assassination plot, the team joins forces with their British counterparts in a special double-episode movie event. Shot on-location in London.

episodes.name: How Piper Got Her Groove Initially
episodes.overview: Piper's awkward college personality is revealed.

episodes.name: Wreck the Malls
episodes.overview: The mall is taken over by a terrorist Mall Santa, trapping Trent's children inside, and locking the rest of the team out of doing some last-minute Christmas shopping.
